# ⚛️ Kelvin Codex Quantum Core

A full-stack quantum-enhanced AI engine for real-time football predictions and auto-betting automation powered by FastAPI, Cirq, and Next.js.

---

![Dashboard Screenshot](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kelvintakpi/Kelvin-Codex-Core/main/screenshots/preview.png)

[![Deploy to Render](https://render.com/images/deploy-to-render-button.svg)](https://render.com/deploy)  
[![Deploy to Vercel](https://vercel.com/button)](https://vercel.com/import)

---

## ✨ Features

- 🔮 Quantum Prediction Engine (Cirq-powered)  
- 🧠 Multi-AI Fusion (DeepSeek, LLaMA integration)  
- 🤖 Auto-Bet with real-time SportyBet API  
- 📊 Realtime Tailwind Dashboard (Next.js + React)  
- ☁️ Deploy-ready for Render & Vercel  

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```bash
kelvin-codex-quantum-core/
├── backend/         # FastAPI server + Quantum logic
├── frontend/        # Next.js Dashboard + Tailwind UI
├── .env.example     # Environment variables template
├── render.yaml      # Render deploy setup config
├── README.md        # This file
````

---

## 🔐 Environment Variables (`.env.example`)

```env
SPORTYBET_API_KEY=your_key_here
QUANTUM_MODE=1
CIRQ_API_ENABLED=true
AUTO_BET=1
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=https://kelvin-codex-backend.onrender.com
```

---

## 🔧 Backend Setup (FastAPI + Cirq)

```bash
cd backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

➡️ Open [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs) for interactive API docs.

---

## 💻 Frontend Setup (Next.js + TailwindCSS)

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

➡️ View frontend at [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

---

## 🚀 Deployment

### Backend (Render)

* Connect your GitHub repo to Render.
* Use the `render.yaml` file for automatic deployment.
* Add environment variables in Render dashboard under the Environment tab.

### Frontend (Vercel)

* Import the `frontend/` folder on Vercel.
* Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE` to your Render backend URL.

